column5: got out to simcoe the other day and got some nice jumbos with one real big hog that im gonna get mounted, made a little video of some of the action        here is a pcture of the hog beside a 2 litre pop bottle to show its true size, makes the pop bottle look small
Look at the size of the belly on that! What a bucketlist fish. Also that ice fishing rod you were using looks awesome, where did you get it from?
Man....that's bigger than most bass I catch
how many inches was that big one?
what kind of fow were u fishing in? looks pretty shallow...
Nice hog!  Did you get a measurement and weight on it?  That thing must have felt like a bass!
The video shows the 2 pound perch at 14".

wow you got a good eye, i built the rod from a broken g-loomis tip.  ya we were fishing shallow anywhere from 5-10 fow the perch are hitting out of aggresion right now and we caught allot of male perch that werent around two weeks ago  when i pinched the tail it was 14 3/8" long and 10.75 giirth she weighed 2 pounds on the dot on the digital scale, funny thing is that the area we were fishing we pulled a couple smallmouth out and i thought thats what i had on
WOW man.  A tru Jumbo.  I'm at work, so I couldnt watch the Video.  I'll check it out when I get home.
Two pound perch,wow,that will look nice on your wall!!!!!!!!!!!!
WOW nice hog man very nice! Was that a little rapala jigging minnow you were using? I was using a soft version, if thats what it was, a few week ago and it produced. Thanks for the pics.
Now that is a piggy perch there. Congrats!
Wow congrats! That there is a perch of a thousand casts!
